Cabinet on Thursday called for South Africa to put up a united front to protect the country s investment grade status just weeks before ratings agencies determine whether the country will be downgraded to junk status. Briefing journalists in parliament a day after Cabinet held its fortnightly meeting, Minister in the Presidency Jeff Radebe reminded South Africans that Moody s, Fitch, and Standard and Poor s will make their decisions over the coming weeks. Government has been working with business, civil society and labour to translate the country s plans into concrete actions that will ensure South Africa remains an investment grade country, he said. Cabinet calls on all sectors to join government in a united front to protect the country s investment status.&#8221; African News Agency